Improved sql query
Implemented recurring jobs that regenerate bookings once an hour
Users can now be created, logged in and logged out.
In user creation, separated user email into email name and email domain
Users are now associated with institutions when created
New bookings generator created

Corrected the room generation algorithm
Bookings made by users are no longer removed during generation

Some graphical changes on index page
Now user bookings are displayed upon login and removed upon logout

Re-designed user system and login system
Prepared this system for more advanced features like, advanced room querying. There is a user page now where all room information is going to be displayed.
Re-designed forms on the users panel.

Implemented some minor changes to how rooms are selected in available rooms area.
Removed the select button and made the entire room html element selectable instead.

Modified the data model to accommodate date of the booking.
Previously there was no way to differentiate between Monday on this week and Monday on next week.

Merge branch 'feature_BookingDates' into develop

Implemented redirects for actions that can only be made by logged in users.

Correct user registration validation
Users with the same email can no longer be created.

Added booking length validations
Bookings minimum length limit and one user can no longer book more then 5 hours worth of bookings.

Added validation on find rooms form
find rooms form will now prevent searches with booking length less then 15 and searches in the past.

minor changes to folder structure
custom classes were moved from the app/model folder to the app/classes folder

Email controller implemented
User activation and reset emails and corresponding controller methods are now setup.

Email controller implemented (Remaining Files)
User activation and reset emails and corresponding controller methods are now setup.

Emails are now sent when user is create
removed some security related files from git

New user validation corrections.
Emails are no longer case sensitive. Also modified email regex to allow dashes properly.
Correct some problems with user creation and case sensitive emails.
Removed works space file (hopefully...)

Prepared the website for heroku deployment
Changed the database used to PostgreSQL and fixed some queries.

Fixed migration bug
The error that appears when migrating from a new database shouldn't exist anymore.
Precompile asset fix
Version with precompiled assets
Database secrets.yml fix
Emailing service corrections for heroku server

Created Procfile
This is used to create a jobs worker on the heroku server.
More email service correction
More email service correction(2)

Scaling change corrections for mobile version
Forms and text are now scaled appropriately on a mobile device.

Guests are now allowed to make bookings.
Available rooms are now displayed on the home page.

Minor corrections to user's unofficial bookings section
It is now displayed above search bookings section. If there are no bookings made then 'NONE' is displayed to indicate that there are no bookings made at the moment.

Added an ability to represent capacity and people for bookings
Capacity is an attribute of a room and it describes the number of people that can fit in a room. People is an attribute of a booking and it describes how many people are associated with that booking.

Search query modifications added
It will now account for the number of people bookings.
Bookings now account for the capacity of the room and the number of people on the booking.
